{{version030}}
{{flavour|Spits acid at a targeted creature.}}

'''Spit Acid''' is a monster-only ability that launches a blob of [[acid]] at a creature, dealing 3d14 acid damage and possibly corroding the target if it hits. As a natural ability, Spit Acid is unaffected by conditions such as [[Silence]] or [[antimagic]].

[[Acid Splash]] is a similar ability unique to [[yellow draconian]]s that also splashes onto creatures adjacent to the target. [[Breathe Acid]] is the player version of said ability.

{{monsters with spell}}

==History==
*Prior to [[0.28]], Spit Acid only dealt 3d7 damage, but there was an extra 4d5 damage against players from "[[Acid#Acidic_Melee_Attacks|acid splash]]". Monsters took 2d4 damage from acid splash instead.
